lrs / listregionscheme        Lists region colour schemes

   Format:
      ;lrs <name>             Lists schemes

   Notes:
      A region colour scheme defines a set of colours for one or more regions.
         The automapper window uses these colours when it draws the region(s).
      This command displays a list of region colour schemes, plus a list of
         any regions that use them.

   User commands:
      lrs / listrs / listregionscheme
